2. Commercial Use Is Allowed

You may use the Software for commercial purposes, including use in commercial products,
hosted services, internal tools, enterprise systems, browser extensions, automation
systems, SDKs, APIs, educational platforms, and white-labeled products, subject to
this license.

3. Bring Your Own Key Required for LLM Execution

If the Software is used as a runtime, execution environment, notebook backend, agent
platform, or any other infrastructure where code (including Lua cells, agent scripts,
extension scripts, or plugin code) is generated, authored, assisted, translated, or
otherwise produced in whole or in part by a Large Language Model ("LLM"), artificial
intelligence system, or similar automated code-generation technology, you MUST provide
end users with Bring Your Own Key ("BYOK") support.

"BYOK support" means that end users must be able to configure and use their own
inference provider credentials, including at minimum:

- their own API key or equivalent credential;
- their own model identifier;
- their own base URL or endpoint URL where applicable;
- provider-specific headers or authentication parameters where reasonably required;
- streaming and non-streaming inference modes where supported by the underlying
  provider and by the Software.

This requirement applies to all LLM-powered features, including but not limited to:
- code generation inside notebook cells;
- agent scripts using the page.*, chrome.*, or web.* APIs;
- automated DOM interaction, navigation, or data extraction;
- plugin-generated code or suggestions;
- any other feature where LLM-generated code is executed within the Software's runtime.

4. Required Provider Compatibility

A commercial offering based on the Software that includes LLM execution must provide
reasonable support for inference providers that implement APIs materially compatible with:

- the OpenAI API; and
- the Anthropic API.

For this license, "materially compatible" means that the provider exposes an API that
can be used through substantially similar request and response semantics, authentication
methods, model identifiers, base URLs, streaming behavior, and message-based inference
patterns.

You may not artificially restrict BYOK support to a single preferred provider, to your
own inference backend, or to providers from which you receive commercial benefit, unless
the user can also configure other materially compatible OpenAI-style or Anthropic-style
providers.

5. No Charging for LLM Usage

You may not charge, meter, resell, mark up, bundle, or otherwise monetize LLM usage,
inference usage, token usage, model access, message credits, AI credits, context-window
usage, output tokens, input tokens, tool-call tokens, reasoning tokens, agent-run credits,
page-action credits, or similar model-consumption or agent-execution units in connection
with the Software.

This prohibition applies regardless of pricing structure, including but not limited to:

- per-token fees;
- per-message fees;
- per-run fees;
- per-cell-execution fees;
- per-agent-action fees (e.g., per click, per snapshot, per navigation);
- AI credit packs;
- usage-based billing;
- model-access tiers;
- subscriptions that include inference usage;
- subscriptions whose price increases based on inference usage;
- bundled plans where LLM usage is part of what the customer is buying;
- resale or markup of third-party inference provider fees.

6. Fees That Are Allowed

You may charge for software, hosting, deployment, maintenance, support, enterprise
features, security features, collaboration features, compliance features, storage,
synchronization, account management, browser extension distribution, workflow
management, notebook sharing, version history, or other non-inference functionality.

However, those fees must not include, meter, resell, mark up, or depend on LLM usage
or agent execution. End users must be able to use their own inference provider
credentials without paying you for LLM usage or agent execution.

7. No Provider Lock-In

You may not remove, disable, obscure, degrade, or materially impair BYOK functionality
for the purpose of forcing users to use your own inference provider, your preferred
provider, your paid inference gateway, or any monetized model-access or agent-execution
service.

8. User Disclosure

Any commercial offering based on the Software that includes LLM execution or agent
functionality must clearly disclose to users that:

- users may bring their own compatible inference provider credentials;
- the offering does not require purchasing LLM usage or agent execution from the provider;
- any LLM usage or agent execution costs are paid directly by the user to their chosen
  inference provider, unless the provider offers free usage independently of the offering.

